,Recommended,237740,8448971,"Posted: 30 December, 2013",all,Whorific,"This game is... interesting. I started out hating this game but quickly started enjoying it. Aside from the sluggish controls, the game is fluid and fun. Paying homage to the great and the horrible games of the NES era, the game has quite a bit of variety but never strays too far from its roots. Being an NES-style game, it's challenging and makes completing a level feel a lot more satisfactory for it, but it's not hard to a point of frustration, at least not on normal difficulty. Being based on James Rolfe's character the Angry Video Game Nerd, the game has a lot of immature humor and unnecessary vulgarity to a point of tedium but if you can look past that, you'll find an enjoyable platformer with a nostalgic feel."
