,Recommended,237740,8703401,"Posted: 14 January, 2014",all,Halflight,"The Angry Video Game Nerd Adventures is a 2D side scroller platform game that features the titular character by James Rolfe in a world that parodies old school games and the web show itself.The various levels of Adventures feature a specific theme and a distinct boss each. You can beat them in any order you wish: once you cleared all the areas you can access the final stage and its boss. Along the levels you can find power-ups and collectables, cameos from internet celebrities and sometime other playable characters with different stats from the Nerd.It's worth mentioning that the game is very difficult. The obstacles are either annoying or plain hard to overcome and a precise timing is often required. On Easy difficulty you have infinite lives and tries and an higher stack of health (as to say, beers). However, starting from Normal difficulty onwards you recive a certain number of lives and tries, culminating in some unlockable difficulties that require you to finish the entire game with three or four lifes or just plain without dying even once.Angry Video Game Nerd Adventures is a challenging game in its own right and will surely please the long time fans of the show due to its numerous references"
