,Recommended,237740,7992603,"Posted: 10 December, 2013",all,metalgearfan1983,"Angry Video Game Nerd Adventures is a love letter to the 8 bit NES era as well as the era that coined and defined the term NES hard! The game puts you in the role of the easily angered, foul mouthed, ill tempered Nerd as he travels through 8 levels of ""Game Land"" inspired by ""Video Game Land"" from the late 80s cartoon ""Captain N: The Game Master"" while the gameplay is inspired by classic retro games like Castlevania, Contra, Mega Man, Ninja Gaiden and others.Each level has various nods to games from the past as well as games that The Nerd has reviewed on his web series. For example, the level ""Beat it And Eat It"" is inspired by the Atari Porn games for the Atari 2600, and the level ""Boo! Haunted House"" inspired by the ""A Nightmare On Elm Street"" and ""Friday The 13th"" NES games!The most satisfying thing about this game is the challenge! Yes, areas of certain levels can be difficult and will even get you to curse like The Nerd himself, but that is what makes this game fun! The process of trial and error while playing through the game and being rewarded for beating the level instead of having you're hand held with a useless guide that shows you how to beat the level or give you recharging health or anything else that current games do nowadays. The game is still very fun as well as rewarding to play and gives you just that right amount of challenge that makes you want to keep on playing til the end!If you are a fan of classic ""NES hard"" games like Castlevania, Contra, Mega Man, or Ninja Gaiden or are a fan of the AVGN character and his web series, then you should definitely get this game!"
