,Recommended,237740,13201633,"Posted: 2 December, 2014",all,ekolis,"Did you enjoy playing Mega Man on the NES as a kid? Then you'll love AVGN Adventures. It's got that same unforgiving challenge (cranked up a bit since you've surely matured in your skill as a gamer since the 1980s), combined with the witty (and quite profane - is this Conker's Bad Fur Day?) humor you'd expect from the Angry Video Game Nerd. This game is hard, but by no means unfair - there is always a path through the level; it's up to you to find it! And of course there are the references to classic games, like the Quickman lasers and space jellyfish in the ""Future 2010"" stage. (Don't worry, you don't need an ice beam to beat the jellyfish!)"
