,Recommended,237740,9558704,"Posted: 19 March, 2014",all,MetalShadowOverlord,"Enjoy classic NES style games such as Megaman or Contra?  Love the AVGN?  Then you'll most likely love this game!  With 9 challenging stages, 6 difficulty levels, and tons of cameo characters, a well as 3 other playable characters and that poopy pickle hiding around the levels to find, replayability is guaranteed!  Even death is hilarious with the Nerd giving his usual scatatonic rants about how bad his own game is (although it can get annoying after the first dozen deaths, as they are unskippable).  Whether you're a veteran fan of the loveable, raging Nerd or have never heard of him until now, you'll definitely enjoy the silly references to both classic and modern AVGN videos.  Worth the buy!"
,Recommended,237740,12589769,"Posted: 20 October, 2014",all,Star,"An excellent platformer. The controls are solid, the levels are semi-varied/creative, the music is flawless, and the secrets are satisfying to find. It is a borderline rage game on the first playthrough, though, as there are a lot of tightly timed maneuvers that'll cause you to die and feel as though you were gypped. The bosses are a tad lackluster, too, as they follow the traditional NES format and have a really, REALLY predictable pattern, with a form of artificial difficulty coming from the speed the boss moves at, and the tight space you have to maneuver in.It's definitely worth its price, though. A very nice platformer for this generation, on par with Shovel Knight."
