,Not Recommended,237740,30381875,Posted: 7 March,all,thainen,"From an AVGN-themed game one would expect an unfair, ultra-hard platformer inspired by the failings of the classic crappy games reviewed by Nerd himself. This is what its creators tried to do -- but, unfortunately, they failed. The game is hard, unfair and frustrating, but not in a good or creative way: it's nothing like I Wanna Be The Guy, where every room screwed with you in a different way. This game relies on one mechanic to make your life living hell: insta-killing blocks, appearing and disappearing in particular intervals of time. This becomes old very fast, and the game has little to offer beyond that. Overall, it's a decent 2d-platformer with lots of jokes borrowed from the show, but there are tons of games in this genre, from Super Meat Boy to VVVVVV that would challenge, enrage and frustrate while also not forgetting to entertain."
