76561198094855510,Recommended,237740,11972021,"Posted: 3 September, 2014",all,BenJammin',"I get angry (no pun intended) kinda quicky when a game frustrates me. And while AVGN Adventures did at first, it quickly became one of my favorite indie platformers ever. While I'm not the biggest fan of AVGN, it's quite interesting to see a game with his type of humor. Controls are tight, graphics are appealing to the eye, sundtrack is great, and the game is quite solid overall. It's like Mega Man in that you can choose any level in a non linear order. While the game is difficult, practice makes perfect, and there are harder difficulty options that will make you pull your hair out (I don't know how anyone could beat YOLO mode). Overall, I really enjoy this game. Short enough to replay a lot, fun to play, and pretty solid game overall. I'll give it an 8/10."
