,Recommended,237740,28171674,"Posted: 3 December, 2016",all,Will The Kill,"This is a fun 2D side scroller, but I'd likely suggest picking it up only if you're a fan of the AVGN series or a fan of really hard 2D side scrollers.  There are a total of nine levels and you can play through the first eight in any order you like; completing those will unlock the final ninth level.  With multiple checkpoints throughout each level, there's a decent amount of challenge to be had in getting through the game.One thing to note here is that if you play the game on any difficulty above easy, you're going to be subject to a life system.  So if you're playing through a level and run out of lives, you have to start back at the very beginning of that level, regardless of the latest checkpoint you got.  This almost made me give up on the game, as the very last stage got to be a bit too challenging for me on normal difficulty with a finite amount of lives to work with.  If you want to change the difficulty, you pretty much have to start over and complete each level again.I ended up beating the first eight levels on normal difficulty, which I thought was a fair challenge, but like I said, the final level was hard enough to make me drop down to easy.  Unfortunately, that meant replaying through the previous eight levels again, although they were much easier to maneuver through on a second run.  The final level was still a challenge, but well worth getting to the end.At the end of the day, if you're familiar with AVGN and the various characters that have appeared in the game, there's plenty of references and funny material to get you through to the end, as well as some really great music and the option to purchase the soundtrack separately.  I do think some of the frustrations in a few areas of the game take the joke of this being a hard game a bit too far, but then again, that's kind of the point - this is supposed to be a very challenging side scroller reminiscent of past generations of video games."
