,Recommended,237740,8415601,"Posted: 29 December, 2013",all,Missingnope.,"This is a game that some people like and hate, mostly for its language. AVGN Adventures is basically like Super Meat Boy, I Wanna Be The Guy, IWBTG Gaiden, and all of the bad games AVGN reviewed had a kid. SMB and IWBTG being the parents. I reccommend that you watch most of the Angry Video Game Nerd's videos to understand most of its contents. AVGN Adventures is one of the hardest games I played. You play as the nerd himself and his (unlockable) characters in Game Land. The game consists of 9 stages: A**holevania, Happy Candy Fun Time, Future F**kballs 2010, Blizard of Balls, Thy Farts Consumed, Dungeons and D**kholes, Beat it and Eat it, Boo! Haunted House, and Laughin' Jokin' Numbnuts (Unlocked after conquering every stage.). Every stage has its own theme, boss, enemy set, and difficulty. Wait, every single stage is hard. I highly reccommend this game. Its fun, difficult, and the language is hilarious."
