,Recommended,237740,12066253,"Posted: 11 September, 2014",all,DragonTroopBeta,"In honour of the upcoming release of AVGN: The Movie, I decided to tackle this one.I'll make it short, partially because the game is also rather short. The game will last you about 4-6 hours, depending on how good you are at platformers, This game is very similar to Megaman 3 when it comes to control, flow, and level design, but even more difficult. If you don't like to die a lot, then a game that is easy to get an achievement for dying 1000 times isn't for you.The game lets you shoot in all directions, except down for some reason. This is a nit-pick worthy note to me, as he does claim to put elements of all his favourite side-scrollers together, which one of them is Super Castlevania 4.All the great AVGN moments are referenced, with the Couch / Guitar guy, Bull♥♥♥♥♥♥Man and even Mike Matei, James' best friend and co-worker, being playable. You will see halarious moments, such as the ""Pitfall first ladder"" rant being heavily enforced. You go down the first ladder in one of the levels, and instantly fall to your death into a chamber of lava, spikes, and flame-sharks (which, by the way, you get to ride later!).The humour is exactly what you would expect from a game written and designed by James Rolfe. Sarcasm levels reach 9001, as the nerd himself will comment on the &quot♥♥♥♥♥♥factor"" of the game. When I was playing the ""Beat it and Eat it"" level, which pays omage his Atari Porn Games episode available only at his website, I hit a slippery spot on theground and fell to my death saying ""God damnit, stupid ice... wait. That's not ice.""Level design is very good, but enemies lack real depth. While the poop jokes were kind of novel in 2007, the just aren't best served wth a dish of platformer.Other minor issues I have found are that sometimes you don't get a chance to read the text. It took me quite a while to find out how to switch characters, as the only time it tells you without going to the option screen to my knowledge is when you meet your first alternate character. Another small problem I ran into was the music bugged out on Blizzard of Balls, looping indefinately until I closed the game entirely. This never reaccured, so it may have been fixed in one of the regular updates Mike and James roll out every few weeks.Over-all, if you are an AVGN fan like me or retro-loving gamers, it's a must-buy at a respectable 8.5/10. For non-fans and platform haters, it's a non-impressing 6/10."
