,Recommended,237740,29134651,Posted: 8 January,all,eXcruciate,"I love Cinemassacre and this game pays great homage to it, and has high enough production value to get a thumbs up. It's fun for a bit, but ultimately I was not a fan of how the game artificially increases the difficulty with death blocks. They do not test your natural gaming skills, instead they exist only to turn the entire game into maddening trial and error. I like to think I did well, making it to the final stage in under 4 hours, but it was never very enjoyable because of repeated sections of levels filled to the brim with anxiety inducing death block patterns. It isn't nearly as hard as some NES games like Battletoads, but it is equally stress inducing and only makes me remember why I hated games like that on the NES.6/10 Average. Will most likely only appeal to AVGN fans. It unfortunately takes its cues from all of the most frustratingly designed NES games, missing a grande opportunity to be its own unique game."
