,Not Recommended,237740,7857800,"Posted: 30 November, 2013",all,Averagus,"While I was expecting a difficult game, I wasn't expecting the deliberately frustrating design of the later levels. The early levels are actually reasonably fair with few surprises that can't be overcome with a bit of skill. The later levels however are designed to kill you over and over and only thorough memorisation will get you through.The retro visuals and soundtrack are impressive and probably the best part of the game. The ""Nerd"" humour is frankly vulgar, childish and often disgusting. A better showcase of the steep decent the series has taken since it has begun, and not what made it so sucessful in the first place.This is a hard one to recommend if you're not a huge fan of the AVGN. If you're looking for a deliberately punishing platformer than you'll want to check out Super Meat Boy. If you've done that and want something more, this probably won't be much more of a challenge. However even long time fans might find this game to be too much; especially if like me, you enjoyed the earlier, tightly edited and genuinely funny series and not long, vulgar nonsense it has become."
