,Not Recommended,237740,9555836,"Posted: 18 March, 2014",all,Jestern,"This may be the hardest game I've ever played, and though it's fun, I have a hard time recomending it.  Mechanically, it has a lot in common with classic NES Mega Man, but the dificulty curve is through the roof.  Its designed to be nearly unbeatable, except through reptition and learning to beat a level the hard way, much like super meat boy.  The art and music are great if you appriciate 8/16 bit era looks and sounds and there are lots of nods to both nerdy culture and classic games that any retro game fan is sure to love.  Sadly, the game is too lude and crude for its own good... It doesnt' try to be witty and instead hopes that you'll find tastless nonsince amuseing, but I didn't.  I'm sure the humor will appeal to someone, but not me, and it will likely appal the average person.  If you love dificult, retro stylized games and can enjoy or ignore course and disguesting content, you'll love this game, especially considering its low price point!  Sadly, for the average gamer looking for old school platformer thrills, i'd have to suggest you instead look to polished, longer, less offensive games like cave story+, super meat boy or rayman."
