76561198179962105,Recommended,237740,19025172,"Posted: 11 November, 2015",all,silverlunastar39,"Holy butts, this game is awesome!I've been a fan of the AVGN since he started, and I've met him a handful of times. He's a really cool guy, so I try to support him in any way that I can. When I heard he had his own game, I jumped at the chance to get it.Simply put, this game is a blast. It's a tough as nails action platformer that perfectly captures the spirit of older gen titles. Kickin' music? Yes. Tight controls? Yes. Colorful, varied stages each with their own theme and challenges? Yes. A play experience that makes me feel like I spent my money well? Yes.If you remember playing games like Contra, Journey to Silius, Mega  Man, and  Super Turrican, this game is for you. It's a simple premise: shoot and jump your way through each stage, all while collecting power ups and dodging an insane amount of obstacles. That's it. And it works. It's the high level of difficulty that makes this game so good though: a very balanced difficulty system allows players of all skill levels to get what they want from this game.Aside from the great gameplay, this is also a fantastic low-brow homage to the games of yesteryear. The incessant profanity made me laugh, too.Buy this game. Expect a torrent of swear words and colorful metaphors to explode from your mouth, but it's a gratifying experience when you finally beat it."
