,Recommended,237740,19404773,"Posted: 30 November, 2015",all,TuxedoOxide,"A game based off of a youtuber sounds risky, even more so when the game is $15, but surprisingly, AVGN Adventures is pretty good despite some issues. The games control is silky smooth (although I reccomend a controller), and the graphics are colorful and full of charecter, and the music is fitting and memorable. The games difficulty is high, but MOSTLY fair. I say mostly because there are points where the game doesn't quite live up to the name, and on higher difficulty modes where lives are few and far between, It's a real hastle when an unexpected instant death block comes on screen, leaving you less than a second to react. Another issue I had with the game is that alot of the games variety of enemies are just clones. I noticed on several occations that I would find an enemy in a stage based off of horror designed like a ghost, and then go to the hell level and find that exact same enemy with a new sprite and same sound effects. Yet another issue I had was that the highly mature and rauchy humor throughout the game is really not very funny. Even when the game quotes the youtube sensation himself, without any context, the jokes just come off as immature and childlike. But even with all of these issues, the game is still really fun, warrenting another playthrough from me. Just be careful with the unlockable difficulties unless you're a masichist."
