,Recommended,237740,8010344,"Posted: 11 December, 2013",all,Manual Danual,"Being a huge AVGN fan I knew I had to own this game, having watched the show since at least 2008.I first started playing it with a keyboard and it was quickly seeming utterly impossible to make it through the first stage I tried. After switching to controller the impossible became much more possible and suddenly I could easily fine-tune my jumps instantly making for a far more enjoyable experience. So I sincerely advise using one with this game.Angry Video Game Nerd Adventures is a side-scrolling action game which offers you that pure sense of accomplishment and rewarding feeling harkening back to the simpler side-scrolling days of old, complete with punishing, somtimes unfair, hand-sweating level design.  The controls are tight and responsive and won't be working against you in any way.  The challenge will seem daunting at times but with patience, observation, familiarity and quick reaction you can make it through. You will fail MANY MANY times but each one is a step forward!There's many references to the show and James Rolfe's content on Cinnamassacre in general.The music is also kick♥♥♥♥♥ retro, catchy bit-chip! You feel like quite the bad♥♥♥♥♥as you play!I recommend this game if you're looking for a hardy, worthy retro challenge!"
