,Recommended,237740,18208621,"Posted: 26 September, 2015",all,trombass08,"First and foremost, if you are not a fan of the Nerd, blue humor, NES hard gameplay, and parody, turn around. This is not the game for you.AVGN Adventures is a love letter to everything that is the Angry Video Game Nerd. You've got the Rolling Rock health display. You've got familiar Cinemassacre characters. You've got Super Mecha Death Christ. You've got Glitch Gremlin. You've got the NES Zapper as your main weapon. You've got hilariously vulgar lines coming from the Nerd at every new element in the game. And you've got homages to some of the Nerd's best moments.As for gameplay, it's kind of like Mega Man in that you run and shoot similar to the Blue Bomber. You also have stage selects before each level and, after defeating the previous bosses, you fight in one final stage that throws everything at you. It also throws in a little bit of Super Mario 2 in having different playable characters with different mechanics.The music is the absolute best part of the game. Each level has a driving theme that's also an homage to a certain game. While my personal favorite is the theme to Future ****balls 2010, the Laughin' Jokin' Numbnuts theme is just crazy.It's not a perfect game at all, but it is more competent and has had more care given to it than most of the games James has played on the show. If you're a fan of the Nerd, you should've already gotten the game by now."
