76561197997255943,Recommended,237740,8044464,"Posted: 14 December, 2013",all,Razzy,"As a person who was watched the AVGN's how since the beginning, it amazes me to see how many (obscure) references have been put into this game. A 2D sidescroller that harkens back to the old SNES days, The Angry Video Game Nerd Adventures is a smorgasboard of James Rolfe's ongoing Youtube sensation and celebrates every second of it.Graphically the game has an inspired look. Meaning that pretty much everything in the game is an homage to something from the show, and the music is probably better than it deserves. While the presentation is top-notch, the gameplay is where the game falters. The game has the tendency to mock the faults of other games: not being able to see oncoming enemies beyond the screen, checkpoints that are placed at sadistic spots and instakills are only the tip of the iceberg. Alot of trial and error is in place here when it shouldn't. If you want to point out the mistakes other games make by being unfair to the player, don't make the same mistakes aswell.Frustration aside, I still think this is a game you should at least give a try. The presentation is great, the soundtrack is unbelievable and it makes for some fun moments. You could do a lot worse."
