76561198034429403,Recommended,237740,17294560,"Posted: 30 July, 2015",all,The King of SMEG,"As a longtime fan of the Angry Video Game Nerd show, I was looking forward to this game when I had heard that it was in development. When I finally got my copy, I realized very quickly that my money was well spent.This game was definitely made with fans of the show in mind, but, it can be enjoyed by anyone who has a love for old school 2D platformers. Angry Video Game Nerd Adventures is a challenging, 2D platformer where you take control of the Nerd himself (or one of the characters that show up on the show, even people like Mike Matei, that you can unlock.)If you have played a platformer on the NES before, you can imagine what you can expect from this. The difference being that it has the AVGN humor, and tropes from the show. For instance, AVGN's main weapon is a NES Zapper. His life are bottles of Rolling Rock. Levels are based on games he has reviewed in the past, even things he has only talked about- Such as the most ridiculous trap room a game developer could ever make... and they made it in this game.The game is a blast to play, and as I said, it is challenging! Although, I do think that there are a few too many checkpoints in the game, and this makes the challenge a little lower-the final levels of the game are madness!So, if you are a fan of AVGN, you will love this. If you are a fan of challenging 2D platformers from the NES era, you will love this.Forewarning, this game is DEFINITELY for the mature gamer. Lots of Swearing and potty humor, so if that isn't your thing, you may want to pass this up as there is quite a lot of it. But, otherwise, this game is a fun throwback to my childhood gaming days, with AVGN's brand of humor, and LOTS of references to the show, even very obscure references, these guys really fit a little bit of everything into this little gem."
