,Not Recommended,237740,26594121,"Posted: 13 November, 2016",all,WillSpringer,"This game has a lot of potential. The mechanics are good, the pixel-graphics are wonderful, and the controls are tight. It would have been a great retro-styled platform game if it weren't so difficult.It seems that the team who made this game decided that making an ultra-difficult game would either be funny, or a fitting homage to the older 8-bit games that many us us grew up with (many of which owe their own difficulty to the quarter-eating business plans of arcdaes).As others have mentioned; death will occur often in this game, and it would have been nice to be placed at the last checkpoint instantly (a la Hotline Miami) instead of being forced to sit through a screen with a ""funny"" AVGN quote after each death. The ""death block"" (tiles in the environment which kill you upon touch) are pretty annoying, and do seem to stem from the developer's need to artificially increase the diffictulty.If you enjoy ultra-difficult games, perhaps you will enjoy this. I found it to be much harder than Contra; maybe more akin to Ninja Gaiden or Battletoads. Overall, I was disappointed because I found this to be more of a test of patience than a proper game."
